1;;;; compiler.lisp - Main compiler interface (T064)
     2;;;; Top-level entry points for compiling Lisp to Wasm
     3
     4(in-package #:clysm/compiler)
     5
     6;;; ============================================================
     7;;; Main Compilation Entry Point
     8;;; ============================================================
     9
    10(defun compile-to-wasm (expr &key output)
    11  "Compile a Lisp expression to Wasm binary.
    12   If OUTPUT is provided, writes to file and returns pathname.
    13   Otherwise returns byte vector.
    14
    15   Feature 022-wasm-import-optimization: Analyzes I/O usage to conditionally
    16   emit Import section only when the compiled code uses I/O functions.
    17
    18   Feature 043: Macro expansion is performed before compilation using the
    19   global macro registry. This handles LOOP, DO, DOLIST, etc.
    20
    21   Examples:
    22     (compile-to-wasm '(+ 1 2))      ; No Import section (no I/O)
    23     (compile-to-wasm '(print 42))   ; Has Import section (uses I/O)
    24     (compile-to-wasm '(+ 1 2) :output \"add.wasm\")"
    25  ;; Feature 043: Expand all macros before compilation
    26  (let* ((expanded-expr (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand-all
    27                          (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:global-macro-registry)
    28                          expr))
    29         (uses-io (clysm/compiler/analyzer/io-usage:analyze-io-usage expanded-expr))
    30         (module (compile-to-module expanded-expr))
    31         (bytes (emit-module module :uses-io uses-io)))
    32    (if output
    33        (progn
    34          (with-open-file (stream output
    35                                  :direction :output
    36                                  :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
    37                                  :if-exists :supersede)
    38            (write-sequence bytes stream))
    39          (pathname output))
    40        bytes)))
    41
    42(defun compile-to-wat (expr)
    43  "Compile a Lisp expression to WAT text format.
    44   Useful for debugging.
    45   Feature 043: Macro expansion is performed before compilation."
    46  ;; Feature 043: Expand all macros before compilation
    47  (let* ((expanded-expr (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:macroexpand-all
    48                          (clysm/compiler/transform/macro:global-macro-registry)
    49                          expr))
    50         (module (compile-to-module expanded-expr)))
    51    (emit-module-wat module)))
    52
    53;;; ============================================================
    54;;; Module Compilation
    55;;; ============================================================
    56
    57(defstruct (compiled-module (:conc-name compiled-module-))
    58  "Compiled Wasm module (compiler's internal representation)"
    59  (types nil :type list)
    60  (functions nil :type list)
    61  (globals nil :type list)
    62  (exports nil :type list)
    63  (main-func-idx nil :type (or null fixnum)))
    64
    65(defun compile-to-module (expr)
    66  "Compile a Lisp expression to a module structure.
    67   Extracts defuns as separate functions and compiles the main body."
    68  ;; Reset lambda state for fresh compilation
    69  (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:reset-lambda-state)
    70  ;; Reset special variable global tracking
    71  (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:reset-special-var-globals)
    72  ;; Clear special variable registry from previous compilations
    73  (clysm/compiler/env:clear-special-variables)
    74  ;; Parse expression to AST (this registers special variables)
    75  (let* ((ast (clysm/compiler/ast:parse-expr expr))
    76         (env (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:make-env))
    77         (module (make-compiled-module))
    78         (functions '())
    79         (defuns '())
    80         (main-forms '()))
    81    ;; Pre-allocate globals for all special variables registered during parsing
    82    ;; This ensures defuns can reference special variables before defvar is compiled
    83    (maphash (lambda (name info)
    84               (declare (ignore info))
    85               (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:allocate-special-var-global name))
    86             clysm/compiler/env:*special-variables*)
    87    ;; Set up runtime globals (NIL, UNBOUND, mv-count, mv-buffer)
    88    (setf (compiled-module-globals module)
    89          (clysm/runtime/objects:generate-runtime-globals))
    90    ;; Reserve index 0 for main function
    91    (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:env-set-function-counter env 1)
    92    ;; First pass: extract defuns and register them
    93    (let ((forms (if (typep ast 'clysm/compiler/ast:ast-progn)
    94                     (clysm/compiler/ast:ast-progn-forms ast)
    95                     (list ast))))
    96      (dolist (form forms)
    97        (if (typep form 'clysm/compiler/ast:ast-defun)
    98            (progn
    99              (push form defuns)
   100              ;; Register function - indices start at 1 (0 is $main)
   101              (let ((name (clysm/compiler/ast:ast-defun-name form)))
   102                (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:env-add-function env name)))
   103            (push form main-forms)))
   104      (setf defuns (nreverse defuns))
   105      (setf main-forms (nreverse main-forms)))
   106    ;; Second pass: compile defuns as separate functions
   107    (dolist (defun-ast defuns)
   108      (let ((func-info (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:compile-defun defun-ast env)))
   109        (push func-info functions)))
   110    (setf functions (nreverse functions))
   111    ;; Compile main function (entry point)
   112    (let* ((main-ast (if (= 1 (length main-forms))
   113                         (first main-forms)
   114                         (clysm/compiler/ast:make-ast-progn :forms main-forms)))
   115           (main-func (compile-main-function main-ast env)))
   116      ;; Main function goes first (index 0)
   117      (setf (compiled-module-functions module) (cons main-func functions))
   118      ;; Compile any pending lambdas and append them
   119      (let ((lambda-funcs (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:compile-pending-lambdas)))
   120        (when lambda-funcs
   121          (setf (compiled-module-functions module)
   122                (append (compiled-module-functions module) lambda-funcs))))
   123      (setf (compiled-module-main-func-idx module) 0)
   124      (setf (compiled-module-exports module)
   125            (list (list "_start" :func 0)))
   126      ;; Add special variable symbol globals (T025)
   127      ;; get-all-special-var-globals returns ((name . index) ...) sorted by index
   128      (let ((special-var-globals (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:get-all-special-var-globals)))
   129        ;; Append symbol globals in order (indices start at 2)
   130        (dolist (entry special-var-globals)
   131          (let ((name (car entry)))
   132            (setf (compiled-module-globals module)
   133                  (append (compiled-module-globals module)
   134                          (list (make-symbol-global name))))))))
   135    module))
   136
   137(defun make-symbol-global (name)
   138  "Create a symbol global for a special variable.
   139   The symbol struct is: (name, value, function, plist)
   140   Uses struct.new_default to initialize all fields to null.
   141   A null value field indicates the variable is unbound.
   142   The type is (ref null 3) for struct.get/set compatibility."
   143  (clysm/backend/sections:make-wasm-global
   144   :name (intern (format nil "$sym_~A" (symbol-name name)))
   145   :type '(:ref-null 3)  ; Nullable reference to symbol struct type
   146   :mutability :var  ; Symbol's value field is mutable
   147   :init-expr '((:struct.new_default 3))))  ; struct.new_default $symbol (type 3)
   148
   149(defun compile-main-function (ast env)
   150  "Compile an AST as the main function."
   151  (let ((instrs (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:compile-to-instructions ast env)))
   152    ;; We need one extra local for the result value to handle null check
   153    (let ((num-locals (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:cenv-local-counter env))
   154          (result-local-idx (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:cenv-local-counter env)))
   155      (list :name '$main
   156            :params nil
   157            :result :i32  ; Return i32 for command-line compatibility
   158            ;; Include locals allocated during body compilation + one for result
   159            :locals (loop for i from 0 to num-locals
   160                          collect (list (gensym "local")
   161                                        (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:env-local-type env i)))
   162            :body (append instrs
   163                          ;; Save result to local for type checking
   164                          (list (list :local.tee result-local-idx))
   165                          ;; Check for null (NIL)
   166                          '(:ref.is_null
   167                            (:if (:result :i32))
   168                            (:i32.const -2147483648))  ; NIL = MIN_INT32 (sentinel)
   169                          '(:else)
   170                          ;; Check if result is a fixnum (i31ref)
   171                          (list (list :local.get result-local-idx))
   172                          '((:ref.test :i31)
   173                            (:if (:result :i32)))
   174                          ;; Is fixnum: extract the value
   175                          (list (list :local.get result-local-idx))
   176                          '((:ref.cast :i31)
   177                            :i31.get_s)
   178                          '(:else)
   179                          ;; Not a fixnum (bignum, ratio, float, complex)
   180                          ;; For now, return a special sentinel to indicate non-fixnum
   181                          ;; TODO: Implement proper printing for bignums
   182                          ;; We'll use MIN_INT32 + 1 (-2147483647) as "non-fixnum" sentinel
   183                          '((:i32.const -2147483647))
   184                          '(:end)
   185                          '(:end))))))
   186
   187;;; ============================================================
   188;;; Module Binary Emission
   189;;; ============================================================
   190
   191(defun get-ffi-import-count ()
   192  "Get the count of FFI imports registered.
   193   001-numeric-functions: Helper for function index offsetting."
   194  (let ((ffi-pkg (find-package :clysm/ffi)))
   195    (if ffi-pkg
   196        (let ((count-fn (find-symbol "GET-FFI-IMPORT-COUNT" ffi-pkg)))
   197          (if count-fn (funcall count-fn) 0))
   198        0)))
   199
   200(defun emit-module (module &key uses-io)
   201  "Emit a compiled module as a Wasm binary byte vector.
   202   USES-IO controls whether Import section is emitted (Feature 022)."
   203  (let ((buffer (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   204                              :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0))
   205        (functions (compiled-module-functions module))
   206        ;; 001-numeric-functions: Get import count for function index offsetting
   207        ;; In Wasm, imports get indices 0 to N-1, local functions get N onwards
   208        (import-offset (get-ffi-import-count)))
   209    ;; Module header (magic + version)
   210    (emit-header buffer)
   211    ;; Type section
   212    (emit-type-section buffer functions)
   213    ;; Import section (T025: FFI imports come after Type, before Function)
   214    ;; Per Wasm spec, section order: Type(1), Import(2), Function(3), ...
   215    ;; 001-numeric-functions: Always check for FFI imports (not just I/O)
   216    ;; Math functions (sin, cos, exp, etc.) are FFI imports but not I/O
   217    ;; Pass function count for correct type index calculation
   218    (emit-import-section-if-needed buffer functions)
   219    ;; Function section
   220    (emit-function-section buffer functions)
   221    ;; Tag section (for exception handling)
   222    (emit-tag-section buffer)
   223    ;; Global section
   224    (when (compiled-module-globals module)
   225      (emit-global-section buffer (compiled-module-globals module)))
   226    ;; Export section (T035: includes both regular exports and FFI exports)
   227    ;; 001-numeric-functions: Offset function indices by import count
   228    (let ((all-exports (append (compiled-module-exports module)
   229                               (or (collect-ffi-exports-for-section) '()))))
   230      (emit-export-section buffer all-exports import-offset))
   231    ;; Element section (for ref.func declarations)
   232    ;; 001-numeric-functions: Offset function indices by import count
   233    (emit-element-section buffer functions import-offset)
   234    ;; Code section
   235    ;; 001-numeric-functions: Pass import-offset for :call instruction handling
   236    (emit-code-section buffer functions import-offset)
   237    ;; Return as simple vector
   238    (coerce buffer '(simple-array (unsigned-byte 8) (*)))))
   239
   240(defun emit-import-section-if-needed (buffer functions)
   241  "Emit Import section if there are FFI imports registered.
   242   T025: Integrate FFI imports into compiler's module generation.
   243   001-numeric-functions: Pass regular function count for correct type indexing.
   244   Uses runtime symbol lookup to avoid compile-time dependency on FFI package."
   245  (let ((ffi-pkg (find-package :clysm/ffi)))
   246    (when ffi-pkg
   247      (let ((env-sym (find-symbol "*FFI-ENVIRONMENT*" ffi-pkg))
   248            (count-fn (find-symbol "GET-FFI-IMPORT-COUNT" ffi-pkg))
   249            (assign-fn (find-symbol "ASSIGN-IMPORT-INDICES" ffi-pkg))
   250            (emit-fn (find-symbol "EMIT-FFI-IMPORTS" ffi-pkg)))
   251        (when (and env-sym (boundp env-sym) count-fn assign-fn emit-fn)
   252          (let ((env (symbol-value env-sym))
   253                ;; 001-numeric-functions: Count non-lambda functions for type index base
   254                (regular-func-count (count-if-not #'is-lambda-function-p functions)))
   255            (when (> (funcall count-fn) 0)
   256              ;; Assign type indices to imports before emitting
   257              ;; 001-numeric-functions: FFI types come after regular function types
   258              (funcall assign-fn env regular-func-count)
   259              ;; Emit the import section
   260              (funcall emit-fn env buffer))))))))
   261
   262(defun collect-ffi-exports-for-section ()
   263  "Collect FFI exports and return them in the format expected by emit-export-section.
   264   T035: Integrate FFI exports into compiler's module generation.
   265   Uses runtime symbol lookup to avoid compile-time dependency on FFI package.
   266   Returns a list of (name kind index) entries."
   267  (let ((ffi-pkg (find-package :clysm/ffi)))
   268    (when ffi-pkg
   269      (let ((env-sym (find-symbol "*FFI-ENVIRONMENT*" ffi-pkg))
   270            (count-fn (find-symbol "GET-FFI-EXPORT-COUNT" ffi-pkg))
   271            (assign-fn (find-symbol "ASSIGN-EXPORT-INDICES" ffi-pkg))
   272            (collect-fn (find-symbol "COLLECT-FFI-EXPORTS" ffi-pkg))
   273            (ed-export-name (find-symbol "ED-EXPORT-NAME" ffi-pkg))
   274            (ed-wrapper-func-index (find-symbol "ED-WRAPPER-FUNC-INDEX" ffi-pkg)))
   275        (when (and env-sym (boundp env-sym) count-fn assign-fn collect-fn
   276                   ed-export-name ed-wrapper-func-index)
   277          (let ((env (symbol-value env-sym)))
   278            (when (> (funcall count-fn) 0)
   279              ;; Assign wrapper function indices
   280              (funcall assign-fn env)
   281              ;; Collect exports and convert to section format
   282              (let ((exports (funcall collect-fn env)))
   283                (mapcar (lambda (decl)
   284                          (list (funcall ed-export-name decl)
   285                                :func
   286                                (or (funcall ed-wrapper-func-index decl) 0)))
   287                        exports)))))))))
   288
   289(defun emit-header (buffer)
   290  "Emit Wasm module header."
   291  ;; Magic number: \0asm
   292  (vector-push-extend #x00 buffer)
   293  (vector-push-extend #x61 buffer)
   294  (vector-push-extend #x73 buffer)
   295  (vector-push-extend #x6D buffer)
   296  ;; Version: 1
   297  (vector-push-extend #x01 buffer)
   298  (vector-push-extend #x00 buffer)
   299  (vector-push-extend #x00 buffer)
   300  (vector-push-extend #x00 buffer))
   301
   302(defun is-lambda-function-p (func)
   303  "Check if a function is a lambda (has $closure as first param)."
   304  (let* ((params (getf func :params))
   305         (first-param-name (when (consp (first params))
   306                             (first (first params)))))
   307    (and first-param-name
   308         (string= (symbol-name first-param-name) "$CLOSURE"))))
   309
   310(defun collect-ffi-type-count ()
   311  "Get the number of FFI types that need to be added to the Type section.
   312   T058: Integration with Type section - count unique FFI function types."
   313  (let ((ffi-pkg (find-package :clysm/ffi)))
   314    (if ffi-pkg
   315        (let ((collect-types-fn (find-symbol "COLLECT-FFI-TYPES" ffi-pkg))
   316              (env-sym (find-symbol "*FFI-ENVIRONMENT*" ffi-pkg)))
   317          (if (and collect-types-fn env-sym (boundp env-sym))
   318              (length (funcall collect-types-fn (symbol-value env-sym)))
   319              0))
   320        0)))
   321
   322(defun emit-ffi-types-to-section (content)
   323  "Emit FFI function types to the Type section content buffer.
   324   T058: Adds function types for FFI imports/exports after regular types.
   325   Each type is emitted as: 0x60 params results (standard func type format)."
   326  (let ((ffi-pkg (find-package :clysm/ffi)))
   327    (when ffi-pkg
   328      (let ((collect-types-fn (find-symbol "COLLECT-FFI-TYPES" ffi-pkg))
   329            (env-sym (find-symbol "*FFI-ENVIRONMENT*" ffi-pkg))
   330            (marshal-type-fn (find-symbol "MARSHAL-TYPE-TO-WASM-TYPE" ffi-pkg)))
   331        (when (and collect-types-fn env-sym (boundp env-sym) marshal-type-fn)
   332          (let ((types (funcall collect-types-fn (symbol-value env-sym))))
   333            (dolist (type-def types)
   334              ;; type-def is (:func (params...) (results...))
   335              (when (and (listp type-def) (eq (first type-def) :func))
   336                (let ((params (second type-def))
   337                      (results (third type-def)))
   338                  ;; Emit function type indicator
   339                  (vector-push-extend #x60 content)
   340                  ;; Emit params
   341                  (emit-leb128-unsigned (length params) content)
   342                  (dolist (p params)
   343                    (emit-ffi-wasm-valtype p content))
   344                  ;; Emit results
   345                  (emit-leb128-unsigned (length results) content)
   346                  (dolist (r results)
   347                    (emit-ffi-wasm-valtype r content)))))))))))
   348
   349(defun emit-ffi-wasm-valtype (type content)
   350  "Emit an FFI Wasm value type to buffer.
   351   T058: Converts FFI Wasm type symbols to Wasm binary encoding.
   352   Handles symbols from any package by comparing symbol names."
   353  (vector-push-extend
   354   (let ((name (if (symbolp type) (symbol-name type) (string type))))
   355     (cond
   356       ((string-equal name "I31REF") #x6C)
   357       ((string-equal name "I32") #x7F)
   358       ((string-equal name "I64") #x7E)
   359       ((string-equal name "F32") #x7D)
   360       ((string-equal name "F64") #x7C)
   361       ((string-equal name "ANYREF") #x6E)
   362       ((string-equal name "EXTERNREF") #x6F)
   363       ((string-equal name "FUNCREF") #x70)
   364       (t (error "Unknown FFI Wasm type: ~A" type))))
   365   content))
   366
   367(defun emit-type-section (buffer functions)
   368  "Emit Type section with GC types and function types.
   369   Layout:
   370   - Types 0-5: GC types ($nil, $unbound, $cons, $symbol, $string, $closure)
   371   - Type 6-7: Reserved
   372   - Types 8-12: Function types ($func_0, $func_1, $func_2, $func_3, $func_N)
   373   - Type 13: Binding frame for special variables
   374   - Type 14: $bignum - arbitrary precision integer (010-numeric-tower)
   375   - Type 15: $ratio - exact rational number (010-numeric-tower)
   376   - Type 16: $float - IEEE 754 double-precision (010-numeric-tower)
   377   - Type 17: $complex - complex number (010-numeric-tower)
   378   - Type 18: $limb_array - array of i32 for bignum limbs (010-numeric-tower)
   379   - Type 19: $tag_lisp_throw - (anyref, anyref) -> () for exception tag
   380   - Type 20: $catch_handler - (anyref, anyref) -> anyref (unused, kept for compatibility)
   381   - Type 21: $catch_result - () -> (anyref, anyref) for catch handler block result
   382   - Type 22: $mv_array - (array (mut anyref)) for multiple values buffer (025-multiple-values)
   383   - Types 23+: Regular (non-lambda) function types + FFI function types (T058)"
   384  (let ((content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   385                               :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0))
   386        ;; Count non-lambda functions (lambdas reuse types 8-12)
   387        (regular-func-count (count-if-not #'is-lambda-function-p functions))
   388        ;; T058: Count FFI function types
   389        (ffi-type-count (collect-ffi-type-count)))
   390    ;; Number of types = 23 (base types) + regular functions + FFI types
   391    (emit-leb128-unsigned (+ 23 regular-func-count ffi-type-count) content)
   392    ;; Type 0: $nil (empty struct)
   393    (emit-gc-struct-type content '())
   394    ;; Type 1: $unbound (empty struct)
   395    (emit-gc-struct-type content '())
   396    ;; Type 2: $cons (car, cdr)
   397    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:anyref t) (:anyref t)))
   398    ;; Type 3: $symbol (name, value, function, plist)
   399    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:anyref nil) (:anyref t) (:anyref t) (:anyref t)))
   400    ;; Type 4: $string (array of i8) - mutable to support make-string
   401    (emit-gc-array-type content :i8 t)
   402    ;; Type 5: $closure (code_0, code_1, code_2, code_N, env)
   403    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:funcref nil) (:funcref nil)
   404                                   (:funcref nil) (:funcref nil)
   405                                   (:anyref t)))
   406    ;; Types 6-7: Reserved (empty placeholders)
   407    (emit-gc-struct-type content '())
   408    (emit-gc-struct-type content '())
   409    ;; Type 8: $func_0 - (ref $closure) -> anyref
   410    (emit-func-type-bytes content '(:anyref) '(:anyref))
   411    ;; Type 9: $func_1 - (ref $closure, anyref) -> anyref
   412    (emit-func-type-bytes content '(:anyref :anyref) '(:anyref))
   413    ;; Type 10: $func_2 - (ref $closure, anyref, anyref) -> anyref
   414    (emit-func-type-bytes content '(:anyref :anyref :anyref) '(:anyref))
   415    ;; Type 11: $func_3 - (ref $closure, anyref, anyref, anyref) -> anyref
   416    (emit-func-type-bytes content '(:anyref :anyref :anyref :anyref) '(:anyref))
   417    ;; Type 12: $func_N - (ref $closure, anyref) -> anyref (list as second param)
   418    (emit-func-type-bytes content '(:anyref :anyref) '(:anyref))
   419    ;; Type 13: $binding_frame - (symbol-ref, old_value, prev) for dynamic bindings
   420    ;; Note: Using anyref for symbol-ref since we can't forward-reference types
   421    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:anyref nil) (:anyref nil) (:anyref nil)))
   422    ;; Type 14: $bignum - (sign:i32, limbs:ref $limb_array) (010-numeric-tower)
   423    ;; Note: limbs field references type 18, but since that's forward, use anyref
   424    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:i32 nil) (:anyref nil)))
   425    ;; Type 15: $ratio - (numerator:anyref, denominator:anyref) (010-numeric-tower)
   426    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:anyref nil) (:anyref nil)))
   427    ;; Type 16: $float - (value:f64) (010-numeric-tower)
   428    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:f64 nil)))
   429    ;; Type 17: $complex - (real:anyref, imag:anyref) (010-numeric-tower)
   430    (emit-gc-struct-type content '((:anyref nil) (:anyref nil)))
   431    ;; Type 18: $limb_array - (array (mut i32)) for bignum limbs (010-numeric-tower)
   432    (emit-gc-array-type content :i32 t)
   433    ;; Type 19: $tag_lisp_throw - (anyref, anyref) -> () for exception tag
   434    (emit-func-type-bytes content '(:anyref :anyref) '())
   435    ;; Type 20: $catch_handler - (anyref, anyref) -> anyref (unused, kept for compatibility)
   436    (emit-func-type-bytes content '(:anyref :anyref) '(:anyref))
   437    ;; Type 21: $catch_result - () -> (anyref, anyref) for catch handler block result
   438    (emit-func-type-bytes content '() '(:anyref :anyref))
   439    ;; Type 22: $mv_array - (array (mut anyref)) for multiple values buffer (025-multiple-values)
   440    (emit-gc-array-type content :anyref t)
   441    ;; Regular function types (indices 23+) - skip lambdas (they use types 8-12)
   442    (dolist (func functions)
   443      (unless (is-lambda-function-p func)
   444        ;; func type indicator
   445        (vector-push-extend #x60 content)
   446        ;; params
   447        (let ((params (getf func :params)))
   448          (emit-leb128-unsigned (length params) content)
   449          (dolist (p params)
   450            (emit-valtype (second p) content)))
   451        ;; results
   452        (let ((result (getf func :result)))
   453          (if result
   454              (progn
   455                (emit-leb128-unsigned 1 content)
   456                (emit-valtype result content))
   457              (emit-leb128-unsigned 0 content)))))
   458    ;; T058: FFI function types (after regular function types)
   459    (emit-ffi-types-to-section content)
   460    ;; Write section
   461    (vector-push-extend 1 buffer)  ; Type section ID
   462    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length content) buffer)
   463    (loop for b across content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))
   464
   465(defun emit-gc-struct-type (buffer fields)
   466  "Emit a GC struct type. Fields is ((valtype mutable-p) ...)"
   467  ;; struct type with subtype: 0x50 0x00 0x5F fields...
   468  ;; Simplified: 0x5F field_count fields...
   469  (vector-push-extend #x5F buffer)  ; struct
   470  (emit-leb128-unsigned (length fields) buffer)
   471  (dolist (field fields)
   472    (emit-valtype (first field) buffer)
   473    (vector-push-extend (if (second field) 1 0) buffer)))  ; mutability
   474
   475(defun emit-gc-array-type (buffer elem-type mutable-p)
   476  "Emit a GC array type."
   477  ;; 0x5E elem_type mutability
   478  (vector-push-extend #x5E buffer)
   479  (emit-valtype elem-type buffer)
   480  (vector-push-extend (if mutable-p 1 0) buffer))
   481
   482(defun emit-func-type-bytes (buffer params results)
   483  "Emit a function type."
   484  (vector-push-extend #x60 buffer)  ; func
   485  (emit-leb128-unsigned (length params) buffer)
   486  (dolist (p params)
   487    (emit-valtype p buffer))
   488  (emit-leb128-unsigned (length results) buffer)
   489  (dolist (r results)
   490    (emit-valtype r buffer)))
   491
   492(defun emit-function-section (buffer functions)
   493  "Emit Function section.
   494   Lambda functions use predefined types 8-12 ($func_0/1/2/3/N).
   495   Regular functions use types 23+ (13 = binding_frame, 14-18 = numeric tower, 19-21 = exception types, 22 = mv_array)."
   496  (let ((content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   497                               :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0))
   498        (regular-func-idx 23))  ; Start regular function types at 23 (after mv_array)
   499    ;; Number of functions
   500    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length functions) content)
   501    ;; Type index for each function
   502    (dolist (func functions)
   503      (if (is-lambda-function-p func)
   504          ;; Lambda functions: use predefined func types 8-12 based on arity
   505          ;; Arity is (length params) - 1 (excluding $closure param)
   506          (let* ((params (getf func :params))
   507                 (arity (1- (length params)))
   508                 (type-idx (case arity
   509                             (0 8)   ; $func_0
   510                             (1 9)   ; $func_1
   511                             (2 10)  ; $func_2
   512                             (3 11)  ; $func_3
   513                             (t 12)))) ; $func_N
   514            (emit-leb128-unsigned type-idx content))
   515          ;; Regular functions: use unique types starting at 23
   516          (progn
   517            (emit-leb128-unsigned regular-func-idx content)
   518            (incf regular-func-idx))))
   519    ;; Write section
   520    (vector-push-extend 3 buffer)  ; Function section ID
   521    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length content) buffer)
   522    (loop for b across content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))
   523
   524(defun emit-tag-section (buffer)
   525  "Emit Tag section for exception handling.
   526   Defines $lisp-throw tag with (param anyref anyref) for (tag-symbol, value).
   527   Tag section has ID 13 and must come after function section."
   528  (let ((content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   529                               :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0)))
   530    ;; Number of tags: 1
   531    (emit-leb128-unsigned 1 content)
   532    ;; Tag 0: $lisp-throw
   533    ;; Format: attribute (0 = exception) + type index
   534    ;; Type index 19 is $tag_lisp_throw - (anyref, anyref) -> ()
   535    (vector-push-extend #x00 content)  ; attribute: exception
   536    (emit-leb128-unsigned 19 content)  ; Use type index 19 ($tag_lisp_throw)
   537    ;; Write section
   538    (vector-push-extend 13 buffer)  ; Tag section ID
   539    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length content) buffer)
   540    (loop for b across content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))
   541
   542(defun emit-global-section (buffer globals)
   543  "Emit Global section (Section ID 6).
   544   Globals: list of wasm-global structs with type, mutability, and init-expr."
   545  (let ((content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   546                               :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0)))
   547    ;; Number of globals
   548    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length globals) content)
   549    ;; Each global: type + mutability + init_expr + end
   550    (dolist (global globals)
   551      (let ((type (clysm/backend/sections:wasm-global-type global))
   552            (mutability (clysm/backend/sections:wasm-global-mutability global))
   553            (init-expr (clysm/backend/sections:wasm-global-init-expr global)))
   554        ;; Global type: valtype
   555        (emit-valtype type content)
   556        ;; Mutability: 0=const, 1=mutable
   557        (vector-push-extend (if (eq mutability :const) 0 1) content)
   558        ;; Init expression
   559        (emit-instructions init-expr content)
   560        ;; End marker
   561        (vector-push-extend #x0B content)))
   562    ;; Write section: ID 6 + size + content
   563    (vector-push-extend 6 buffer)  ; Global section ID
   564    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length content) buffer)
   565    (loop for b across content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))
   566
   567(defun emit-export-section (buffer exports &optional (import-offset 0))
   568  "Emit Export section.
   569   IMPORT-OFFSET is added to function indices to account for FFI imports.
   570   001-numeric-functions: FFI imports get indices 0 to N-1, local functions get N onwards."
   571  (let ((content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   572                               :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0)))
   573    ;; Number of exports
   574    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length exports) content)
   575    ;; Each export
   576    (dolist (export exports)
   577      (destructuring-bind (name kind index) export
   578        ;; Name (length-prefixed UTF-8)
   579        (let ((name-bytes (clysm/lib/utf8:string-to-utf8-octets name)))
   580          (emit-leb128-unsigned (length name-bytes) content)
   581          (loop for b across name-bytes do (vector-push-extend b content)))
   582        ;; Export kind
   583        (vector-push-extend (ecase kind (:func 0) (:table 1) (:memory 2) (:global 3)) content)
   584        ;; Index - offset function indices by import count
   585        (let ((final-index (if (eq kind :func)
   586                               (+ index import-offset)
   587                               index)))
   588          (emit-leb128-unsigned final-index content))))
   589    ;; Write section
   590    (vector-push-extend 7 buffer)  ; Export section ID
   591    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length content) buffer)
   592    (loop for b across content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))
   593
   594(defun emit-element-section (buffer functions &optional (import-offset 0))
   595  "Emit Element section with declarative segment for lambda functions.
   596   This allows ref.func to reference lambda functions.
   597   IMPORT-OFFSET is added to function indices to account for FFI imports.
   598   001-numeric-functions: FFI imports get indices 0 to N-1, local functions get N onwards."
   599  ;; Collect lambda function indices
   600  (let ((lambda-indices '()))
   601    (loop for func in functions
   602          for i from 0
   603          do (when (is-lambda-function-p func)
   604               (push i lambda-indices)))
   605    ;; Only emit if there are lambda functions
   606    (when lambda-indices
   607      (setf lambda-indices (nreverse lambda-indices))
   608      (let ((content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   609                                   :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0)))
   610        ;; Number of element segments
   611        (emit-leb128-unsigned 1 content)
   612        ;; Declarative element segment (flag 0x03)
   613        ;; Format: 0x03 elemkind vec(funcidx)
   614        (vector-push-extend #x03 content)  ; declarative, uses indices
   615        (vector-push-extend #x00 content)  ; elemkind = funcref
   616        ;; Number of function indices
   617        (emit-leb128-unsigned (length lambda-indices) content)
   618        ;; Function indices - offset by import count
   619        (dolist (idx lambda-indices)
   620          (emit-leb128-unsigned (+ idx import-offset) content))
   621        ;; Write section
   622        (vector-push-extend 9 buffer)  ; Element section ID
   623        (emit-leb128-unsigned (length content) buffer)
   624        (loop for b across content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))))
   625
   626(defun emit-code-section (buffer functions &optional (import-offset 0))
   627  "Emit Code section.
   628   IMPORT-OFFSET is added to local function :call indices.
   629   001-numeric-functions: Distinguishes FFI :call-import from local :call."
   630  (let ((content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   631                               :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0)))
   632    ;; Number of function bodies
   633    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length functions) content)
   634    ;; Each function body
   635    (dolist (func functions)
   636      (emit-function-body func content import-offset))
   637    ;; Write section
   638    (vector-push-extend 10 buffer)  ; Code section ID
   639    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length content) buffer)
   640    (loop for b across content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))
   641
   642(defun emit-function-body (func buffer &optional (import-offset 0))
   643  "Emit a function body.
   644   IMPORT-OFFSET is added to local function :call indices."
   645  (let ((body-content (make-array 0 :element-type '(unsigned-byte 8)
   646                                    :adjustable t :fill-pointer 0)))
   647    ;; Locals (grouped by type)
   648    (let ((locals (getf func :locals)))
   649      (emit-leb128-unsigned (length locals) body-content)
   650      (dolist (local locals)
   651        (emit-leb128-unsigned 1 body-content)
   652        (emit-valtype (second local) body-content)))
   653    ;; Instructions
   654    (let ((instrs (getf func :body)))
   655      (emit-instructions instrs body-content import-offset))
   656    ;; End
   657    (vector-push-extend #x0B body-content)
   658    ;; Write size + content
   659    (emit-leb128-unsigned (length body-content) buffer)
   660    (loop for b across body-content do (vector-push-extend b buffer))))
   661
   662(defun emit-instructions (instrs buffer &optional (import-offset 0))
   663  "Emit a list of instructions after resolving symbolic labels.
   664   IMPORT-OFFSET is added to local function :call indices."
   665  (let ((resolved (resolve-labels instrs)))
   666    (dolist (instr resolved)
   667      (emit-instruction instr buffer import-offset))))
   668
   669;;; ============================================================
   670;;; Label Resolution
   671;;; ============================================================
   672;;;
   673;;; Wasm uses relative branch indices - an index of 0 means the innermost
   674;;; enclosing block/loop, 1 means the next outer, etc.
   675;;;
   676;;; Instructions like (:block $label type) and (:loop $label type) introduce
   677;;; labels. (:br $label) and (:br_if $label) reference them.
   678;;;
   679;;; This pass converts symbolic labels to numeric indices.
   680
   681(defun resolve-labels (instrs)
   682  "Resolve symbolic labels in instructions to numeric branch indices."
   683  (let ((label-stack '()))  ; Stack of (label . depth-introduced)
   684    (resolve-labels-in-list instrs label-stack 0)))
   685
   686(defun resolve-labels-in-list (instrs label-stack depth)
   687  "Resolve labels in a flat list of instructions."
   688  (let ((result '())
   689        (current-depth depth)
   690        (current-labels label-stack))
   691    (dolist (instr instrs)
   692      (cond
   693        ;; Block with label: (:block $label type)
   694        ((and (consp instr) (eq (car instr) :block)
   695              (symbolp (cadr instr))
   696              (not (null (cadr instr))))
   697         (let* ((label (cadr instr))
   698                (block-type (caddr instr)))
   699           ;; Push label with current depth
   700           (push (cons label current-depth) current-labels)
   701           (incf current-depth)
   702           ;; Emit block with just the type
   703           (push (list :block block-type) result)))
   704        ;; Loop with label: (:loop $label type)
   705        ((and (consp instr) (eq (car instr) :loop)
   706              (symbolp (cadr instr))
   707              (not (null (cadr instr))))
   708         (let* ((label (cadr instr))
   709                (loop-type (caddr instr)))
   710           ;; Push label with current depth
   711           (push (cons label current-depth) current-labels)
   712           (incf current-depth)
   713           ;; Emit loop with just the type
   714           (push (list :loop loop-type) result)))
   715        ;; Block/loop without label (just type)
   716        ((and (consp instr) (member (car instr) '(:block :loop))
   717              (or (null (cadr instr))
   718                  (and (listp (cadr instr)) (eq (caar (cdr instr)) :result))
   719                  (and (listp (cadr instr)) (eq (caar (cdr instr)) :type))))
   720         (incf current-depth)
   721         (push instr result))
   722        ;; If also introduces a block scope
   723        ((and (consp instr) (eq (car instr) :if))
   724         (incf current-depth)
   725         (push instr result))
   726        ;; try_table also introduces a block scope
   727        ((and (consp instr) (eq (car instr) :try_table))
   728         (incf current-depth)
   729         (push instr result))
   730        ;; End decreases depth
   731        ((eq instr :end)
   732         (decf current-depth)
   733         ;; Pop labels that were at this depth
   734         (loop while (and current-labels
   735                          (= (cdar current-labels) current-depth))
   736               do (pop current-labels))
   737         (push instr result))
   738        ;; Branch with symbolic label: (:br $label)
   739        ((and (consp instr) (eq (car instr) :br)
   740              (symbolp (cadr instr)))
   741         (let* ((label (cadr instr))
   742                (entry (assoc label current-labels)))
   743           (if entry
   744               ;; Calculate relative index
   745               (let ((target-depth (cdr entry)))
   746                 (push (list :br (- current-depth target-depth 1)) result))
   747               (error "Unknown branch label: ~A" label))))
   748        ;; Branch-if with symbolic label: (:br_if $label)
   749        ((and (consp instr) (eq (car instr) :br_if)
   750              (symbolp (cadr instr)))
   751         (let* ((label (cadr instr))
   752                (entry (assoc label current-labels)))
   753           (if entry
   754               (let ((target-depth (cdr entry)))
   755                 (push (list :br_if (- current-depth target-depth 1)) result))
   756               (error "Unknown branch label: ~A" label))))
   757        ;; Everything else passes through unchanged
   758        (t
   759         (push instr result))))
   760    (nreverse result)))
   761
   762(defun emit-instruction (instr buffer &optional (import-offset 0))
   763  "Emit a single instruction.
   764   IMPORT-OFFSET is added to local function indices for :call, :return_call, :ref.func.
   765   001-numeric-functions: :call-import is used for FFI calls (no offset)."
   766  (cond
   767    ;; List instructions (with operands)
   768    ((consp instr)
   769     (let ((op (car instr)))
   770       (case op
   771         (:i32.const
   772          (vector-push-extend #x41 buffer)
   773          (emit-leb128-signed (cadr instr) buffer))
   774         (:i64.const
   775          (vector-push-extend #x42 buffer)
   776          (emit-leb128-signed (cadr instr) buffer))
   777         ;; Float constants (010-numeric-tower)
   778         (:f32.const
   779          (vector-push-extend #x43 buffer)
   780          (emit-f32 (cadr instr) buffer))
   781         (:f64.const
   782          (vector-push-extend #x44 buffer)
   783          (emit-f64 (cadr instr) buffer))
   784         (:local.get
   785          (vector-push-extend #x20 buffer)
   786          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   787         (:local.set
   788          (vector-push-extend #x21 buffer)
   789          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   790         (:local.tee
   791          (vector-push-extend #x22 buffer)
   792          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   793         (:global.get
   794          (vector-push-extend #x23 buffer)
   795          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   796         (:global.set
   797          (vector-push-extend #x24 buffer)
   798          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   799         (:call
   800          ;; Call to local function - add import-offset
   801          ;; 001-numeric-functions: Local functions start at index import-offset
   802          (vector-push-extend #x10 buffer)
   803          (emit-leb128-unsigned (+ (cadr instr) import-offset) buffer))
   804         (:call-import
   805          ;; Call to FFI import - no offset needed
   806          ;; 001-numeric-functions: Imports use indices 0 to N-1 directly
   807          (vector-push-extend #x10 buffer)
   808          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   809         (:if
   810          (vector-push-extend #x04 buffer)
   811          ;; Block type
   812          (emit-block-type (cadr instr) buffer))
   813         (:ref.null
   814          ;; ref.null <heaptype>
   815          (vector-push-extend #xD0 buffer)
   816          (emit-heaptype (cadr instr) buffer))
   817         (:ref.cast
   818          ;; ref.cast <reftype> - cast reference to specific type
   819          ;; Uses nullable variant (0xFB 0x16) to handle nil inputs
   820          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   821          (vector-push-extend #x16 buffer)  ; ref.cast nullable opcode
   822          (emit-heaptype-for-gc (cadr instr) buffer))
   823         (:ref.test
   824          ;; ref.test <reftype> - test if reference is of type
   825          ;; Uses nullable variant (0xFB 0x14) to handle nil inputs
   826          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   827          (vector-push-extend #x14 buffer)  ; ref.test nullable opcode
   828          (emit-heaptype-for-gc (cadr instr) buffer))
   829         (:ref.func
   830          ;; ref.func <funcidx> - get function reference
   831          ;; 001-numeric-functions: Add import-offset for local functions
   832          (vector-push-extend #xD2 buffer)
   833          (emit-leb128-unsigned (+ (cadr instr) import-offset) buffer))
   834         (:struct.new
   835          ;; struct.new <typeidx> - create new struct
   836          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   837          (vector-push-extend #x00 buffer)
   838          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   839         (:struct.new_default
   840          ;; struct.new_default <typeidx> - create struct with default values
   841          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   842          (vector-push-extend #x01 buffer)
   843          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   844         (:struct.get
   845          ;; struct.get <typeidx> <fieldidx> - get field from struct
   846          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   847          (vector-push-extend #x02 buffer)
   848          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer)   ; type index
   849          (emit-leb128-unsigned (caddr instr) buffer)) ; field index
   850         (:struct.set
   851          ;; struct.set <typeidx> <fieldidx> - set field in struct
   852          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   853          (vector-push-extend #x05 buffer)
   854          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer)   ; type index
   855          (emit-leb128-unsigned (caddr instr) buffer)) ; field index
   856         (:array.new_fixed
   857          ;; array.new_fixed <typeidx> <n> - create array with n elements from stack
   858          ;; 008-character-string: Used for string literals
   859          ;; Opcode: 0xFB 0x08
   860          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   861          (vector-push-extend #x08 buffer)
   862          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer)   ; type index
   863          (emit-leb128-unsigned (caddr instr) buffer)) ; n elements
   864         (:array.new_default
   865          ;; array.new_default <typeidx> - create array with default values
   866          ;; 008-character-string: Used for make-string
   867          ;; Stack: [size:i32] -> [arrayref]
   868          ;; Opcode: 0xFB 0x07
   869          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   870          (vector-push-extend #x07 buffer)
   871          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))  ; type index
   872         (:array.set
   873          ;; array.set <typeidx> - set element in array
   874          ;; 008-character-string: Used for make-string fill
   875          ;; Stack: [arrayref, idx:i32, value] -> []
   876          ;; Opcode: 0xFB 0x0E
   877          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   878          (vector-push-extend #x0E buffer)
   879          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))  ; type index
   880         (:array.len
   881          ;; array.len - get length of array
   882          ;; 008-character-string: Used for string length
   883          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   884          (vector-push-extend #x0F buffer))
   885         (:array.get
   886          ;; array.get <typeidx> - get element from array (for anyref)
   887          ;; 025-multiple-values: Used for accessing mv-buffer
   888          ;; Stack: [arrayref, idx:i32] -> [value]
   889          ;; Opcode: 0xFB 0x0B
   890          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   891          (vector-push-extend #x0B buffer)
   892          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   893        (:array.get_u
   894          ;; array.get_u <typeidx> - get unsigned element from array
   895          ;; 008-character-string: Used for char/schar
   896          (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
   897          (vector-push-extend #x0D buffer)
   898          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   899         (:call_ref
   900          ;; call_ref <typeidx> - call through function reference
   901          (vector-push-extend #x14 buffer)
   902          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   903         (:return_call
   904          ;; return_call <funcidx> - tail call to known function (TCO)
   905          ;; 001-numeric-functions: Add import-offset for local functions
   906          ;; Opcode: 0x12
   907          (vector-push-extend #x12 buffer)
   908          (emit-leb128-unsigned (+ (cadr instr) import-offset) buffer))
   909         (:return_call_ref
   910          ;; return_call_ref <typeidx> - tail call through function reference (TCO)
   911          ;; Opcode: 0x15
   912          (vector-push-extend #x15 buffer)
   913          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   914         (:block
   915          ;; block <blocktype> - start block
   916          (vector-push-extend #x02 buffer)
   917          (emit-block-type (cadr instr) buffer))
   918         (:loop
   919          ;; loop <blocktype> - start loop
   920          (vector-push-extend #x03 buffer)
   921          (emit-block-type (cadr instr) buffer))
   922         (:br
   923          ;; br <labelidx> - branch
   924          (vector-push-extend #x0C buffer)
   925          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   926         (:br_if
   927          ;; br_if <labelidx> - conditional branch
   928          (vector-push-extend #x0D buffer)
   929          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   930         (:br_table
   931          ;; br_table <vec(labelidx)> <labelidx> - table branch
   932          (vector-push-extend #x0E buffer)
   933          (let ((labels (cdr instr)))
   934            ;; vec length (excluding default)
   935            (emit-leb128-unsigned (1- (length labels)) buffer)
   936            ;; label indices
   937            (dolist (label labels)
   938              (emit-leb128-unsigned label buffer))))
   939         ;; Exception handling instructions
   940         (:try_table
   941          ;; try_table <blocktype> <vec(catch)> - structured exception handling
   942          ;; Format: 0x1F blocktype vec(catch_clause)
   943          ;; catch_clause: 0x00 tagidx labelidx (catch)
   944          ;;            or 0x01 tagidx labelidx (catch_ref)
   945          ;;            or 0x02 labelidx (catch_all)
   946          ;;            or 0x03 labelidx (catch_all_ref)
   947          (vector-push-extend #x1F buffer)
   948          ;; Block type (result type)
   949          (emit-block-type (cadr instr) buffer)
   950          ;; Catch clauses - rest of args are catch clauses
   951          (let ((clauses (cddr instr)))
   952            (emit-leb128-unsigned (length clauses) buffer)
   953            (dolist (clause clauses)
   954              (ecase (car clause)
   955                (:catch
   956                 ;; (:catch tagidx labelidx)
   957                 (vector-push-extend #x00 buffer)
   958                 (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr clause) buffer)
   959                 (emit-leb128-unsigned (caddr clause) buffer))
   960                (:catch_ref
   961                 ;; (:catch_ref tagidx labelidx)
   962                 (vector-push-extend #x01 buffer)
   963                 (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr clause) buffer)
   964                 (emit-leb128-unsigned (caddr clause) buffer))
   965                (:catch_all
   966                 ;; (:catch_all labelidx)
   967                 (vector-push-extend #x02 buffer)
   968                 (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr clause) buffer))
   969                (:catch_all_ref
   970                 ;; (:catch_all_ref labelidx)
   971                 (vector-push-extend #x03 buffer)
   972                 (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr clause) buffer))))))
   973         (:throw
   974          ;; throw <tagidx> - throw exception
   975          (vector-push-extend #x08 buffer)
   976          (emit-leb128-unsigned (cadr instr) buffer))
   977         (:throw_ref
   978          ;; throw_ref - rethrow exception from exnref
   979          (vector-push-extend #x0A buffer))
   980         (otherwise
   981          (error "Unknown compound instruction: ~A" op)))))
   982    ;; Simple keyword instructions
   983    ((keywordp instr)
   984     (case instr
   985       (:unreachable (vector-push-extend #x00 buffer))
   986       (:nop (vector-push-extend #x01 buffer))
   987       (:end (vector-push-extend #x0B buffer))
   988       (:else (vector-push-extend #x05 buffer))
   989       (:drop (vector-push-extend #x1A buffer))
   990       (:return (vector-push-extend #x0F buffer))
   991       ;; i32 operations
   992       (:i32.eqz (vector-push-extend #x45 buffer))
   993       (:i32.eq (vector-push-extend #x46 buffer))
   994       (:i32.ne (vector-push-extend #x47 buffer))
   995       (:i32.lt_s (vector-push-extend #x48 buffer))
   996       (:i32.lt_u (vector-push-extend #x49 buffer))
   997       (:i32.gt_s (vector-push-extend #x4A buffer))
   998       (:i32.gt_u (vector-push-extend #x4B buffer))
   999       (:i32.le_s (vector-push-extend #x4C buffer))
  1000       (:i32.le_u (vector-push-extend #x4D buffer))
  1001       (:i32.ge_s (vector-push-extend #x4E buffer))
  1002       (:i32.ge_u (vector-push-extend #x4F buffer))
  1003       (:i32.add (vector-push-extend #x6A buffer))
  1004       (:i32.sub (vector-push-extend #x6B buffer))
  1005       (:i32.mul (vector-push-extend #x6C buffer))
  1006       (:i32.div_s (vector-push-extend #x6D buffer))
  1007       (:i32.div_u (vector-push-extend #x6E buffer))
  1008       (:i32.rem_s (vector-push-extend #x6F buffer))
  1009       (:i32.rem_u (vector-push-extend #x70 buffer))
  1010       (:i32.and (vector-push-extend #x71 buffer))
  1011       (:i32.or (vector-push-extend #x72 buffer))
  1012       (:i32.xor (vector-push-extend #x73 buffer))
  1013       (:i32.shl (vector-push-extend #x74 buffer))
  1014       (:i32.shr_s (vector-push-extend #x75 buffer))
  1015       (:i32.shr_u (vector-push-extend #x76 buffer))
  1016       ;; i32 unary operations (001-numeric-functions)
  1017       (:i32.clz (vector-push-extend #x67 buffer))
  1018       (:i32.ctz (vector-push-extend #x68 buffer))
  1019       (:i32.popcnt (vector-push-extend #x69 buffer))
  1020       ;; i64 operations (024-equality-predicates)
  1021       (:i64.eq (vector-push-extend #x51 buffer))
  1022       (:i64.ne (vector-push-extend #x52 buffer))
  1023       ;; f64 operations (023-type-predicates)
  1024       (:f64.eq (vector-push-extend #x61 buffer))
  1025       (:f64.ne (vector-push-extend #x62 buffer))
  1026       (:f64.lt (vector-push-extend #x63 buffer))
  1027       (:f64.gt (vector-push-extend #x64 buffer))
  1028       (:f64.le (vector-push-extend #x65 buffer))
  1029       (:f64.ge (vector-push-extend #x66 buffer))
  1030       ;; f64 conversion (024-equality-predicates)
  1031       (:f64.convert_i32_s (vector-push-extend #xB7 buffer))
  1032       (:f64.convert_i32_u (vector-push-extend #xB8 buffer))
  1033       ;; Reference operations
  1034       (:ref.eq (vector-push-extend #xD3 buffer))
  1035       (:ref.is_null (vector-push-extend #xD1 buffer))
  1036       ;; GC operations (0xFB prefix)
  1037       (:ref.i31
  1038        (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
  1039        (vector-push-extend #x1C buffer))
  1040       (:i31.get_s
  1041        (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
  1042        (vector-push-extend #x1D buffer))
  1043       (:i31.get_u
  1044        (vector-push-extend #xFB buffer)
  1045        (vector-push-extend #x1E buffer))
  1046       (otherwise
  1047        (error "Unknown instruction: ~A" instr))))
  1048    (t
  1049     (error "Invalid instruction format: ~A" instr))))
  1050
  1051(defun emit-block-type (block-type buffer)
  1052  "Emit a block type."
  1053  (cond
  1054    ((null block-type)
  1055     ;; Empty block type
  1056     (vector-push-extend #x40 buffer))
  1057    ((and (listp block-type) (eq (car block-type) :result))
  1058     ;; Result type
  1059     (emit-valtype (cadr block-type) buffer))
  1060    ((and (listp block-type) (eq (car block-type) :type))
  1061     ;; Type index for multi-value blocks
  1062     ;; (:type N) means use type index N
  1063     (emit-leb128-signed (cadr block-type) buffer))
  1064    (t
  1065     (error "Unknown block type: ~A" block-type))))
  1066
  1067(defun emit-valtype (type buffer)
  1068  "Emit a value type."
  1069  (cond
  1070    ;; Compound reference type: (:ref-null typeidx)
  1071    ((and (listp type) (eq (car type) :ref-null))
  1072     (vector-push-extend #x63 buffer)  ; refnull
  1073     (emit-leb128-signed (cadr type) buffer))
  1074    ;; Compound reference type: (:ref typeidx) - non-nullable
  1075    ((and (listp type) (eq (car type) :ref))
  1076     (vector-push-extend #x64 buffer)  ; ref
  1077     (emit-leb128-signed (cadr type) buffer))
  1078    ;; Simple types
  1079    ((keywordp type)
  1080     (vector-push-extend
  1081      (ecase type
  1082        (:i32 #x7F)
  1083        (:i64 #x7E)
  1084        (:f32 #x7D)
  1085        (:f64 #x7C)
  1086        (:i8 #x78)         ; packed i8 for arrays
  1087        (:i16 #x77)        ; packed i16 for arrays
  1088        (:anyref #x6E)     ; any heap type - parent of GC types
  1089        (:externref #x6F)  ; external references - separate hierarchy
  1090        (:funcref #x70)
  1091        (:i31ref #x6C)
  1092        (:eqref #x6D)
  1093        (:exnref #x69))    ; exception reference (exception handling proposal)
  1094      buffer))
  1095    (t
  1096     (error "Unknown value type: ~A" type))))
  1097
  1098(defun emit-heaptype (type buffer)
  1099  "Emit a heap type for ref.null, ref.cast, etc.
  1100   Can be a keyword (abstract type), a number (type index), or (ref N) for concrete types."
  1101  (cond
  1102    ;; Numeric type index - emit as signed LEB128
  1103    ((integerp type)
  1104     (emit-leb128-signed type buffer))
  1105    ;; List form: (ref <type-index>) for concrete reference types
  1106    ((and (listp type) (eq (first type) :ref))
  1107     (let ((type-idx (second type)))
  1108       (emit-leb128-signed type-idx buffer)))
  1109    ;; Keyword type
  1110    ((keywordp type)
  1111     (vector-push-extend
  1112      (ecase type
  1113        (:none #x71)       ; bottom type for null
  1114        (:nofunc #x73)     ; bottom type for func
  1115        (:noextern #x72)   ; bottom type for extern
  1116        (:any #x6E)
  1117        (:eq #x6D)
  1118        (:i31 #x6C)
  1119        (:struct #x6B)
  1120        (:array #x6A)
  1121        (:func #x70)
  1122        (:extern #x6F)
  1123        (:exn #x69))       ; exception heap type
  1124      buffer))
  1125    (t
  1126     (error "Unknown heap type: ~A" type))))
  1127
  1128(defun emit-heaptype-for-gc (type buffer)
  1129  "Emit a heaptype for ref.cast/ref.test GC instructions.
  1130   Extracts the heaptype from reftype forms like (:ref 2)."
  1131  (cond
  1132    ;; List form: (:ref <type-idx>) - extract type index
  1133    ((and (listp type) (eq (first type) :ref))
  1134     (emit-leb128-signed (second type) buffer))
  1135    ;; List form: (:ref-null <type-idx>) - extract type index
  1136    ((and (listp type) (eq (first type) :ref-null))
  1137     (emit-leb128-signed (second type) buffer))
  1138    ;; Abstract heap types (i31, eq, any, etc.)
  1139    ((keywordp type)
  1140     (emit-heaptype type buffer))
  1141    ;; Numeric type index
  1142    ((integerp type)
  1143     (emit-leb128-signed type buffer))
  1144    (t
  1145     (error "Unknown ref type: ~A" type))))
  1146
  1147(defun emit-leb128-unsigned (value buffer)
  1148  "Emit an unsigned LEB128 encoded value."
  1149  (loop
  1150    (let ((byte (logand value #x7F)))
  1151      (setf value (ash value -7))
  1152      (if (zerop value)
  1153          (progn
  1154            (vector-push-extend byte buffer)
  1155            (return))
  1156          (vector-push-extend (logior byte #x80) buffer)))))
  1157
  1158(defun emit-leb128-signed (value buffer)
  1159  "Emit a signed LEB128 encoded value."
  1160  (let ((more t))
  1161    (loop while more do
  1162      (let ((byte (logand value #x7F)))
  1163        (setf value (ash value -7))
  1164        (let ((sign-bit (if (logbitp 6 byte) 1 0)))
  1165          (if (or (and (zerop value) (zerop sign-bit))
  1166                  (and (= value -1) (= sign-bit 1)))
  1167              (progn
  1168                (vector-push-extend byte buffer)
  1169                (setf more nil))
  1170              (vector-push-extend (logior byte #x80) buffer)))))))
  1171
  1172;;; ============================================================
  1173;;; Float Encoding (010-numeric-tower)
  1174;;; ============================================================
  1175
  1176(defun emit-f32 (value buffer)
  1177  "Emit an IEEE 754 single-precision (32-bit) float in little-endian."
  1178  (let* ((float32 (coerce value 'single-float))
  1179         (bits (sb-kernel:single-float-bits float32)))
  1180    (vector-push-extend (logand bits #xFF) buffer)
  1181    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -8) #xFF) buffer)
  1182    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -16) #xFF) buffer)
  1183    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -24) #xFF) buffer)))
  1184
  1185(defun emit-f64 (value buffer)
  1186  "Emit an IEEE 754 double-precision (64-bit) float in little-endian."
  1187  (let* ((float64 (coerce value 'double-float))
  1188         (bits (sb-kernel:double-float-bits float64)))
  1189    (vector-push-extend (logand bits #xFF) buffer)
  1190    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -8) #xFF) buffer)
  1191    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -16) #xFF) buffer)
  1192    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -24) #xFF) buffer)
  1193    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -32) #xFF) buffer)
  1194    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -40) #xFF) buffer)
  1195    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -48) #xFF) buffer)
  1196    (vector-push-extend (logand (ash bits -56) #xFF) buffer)))
  1197
  1198;;; ============================================================
  1199;;; WAT Output (for debugging)
  1200;;; ============================================================
  1201
  1202(defun emit-instr-wat (stream instr indent)
  1203  "Emit a single instruction in WAT format."
  1204  (let ((spaces (make-string indent :initial-element #\Space)))
  1205    (cond
  1206      ;; Keyword (simple instruction like :ref.is_null)
  1207      ((keywordp instr)
  1208       (format stream "~A~A~%" spaces (string-downcase (symbol-name instr))))
  1209      ;; List starting with keyword (instruction with operands)
  1210      ((and (listp instr) (keywordp (first instr)))
  1211       (let ((op (first instr))
  1212             (args (rest instr)))
  1213         (cond
  1214           ;; Block instructions (if, block, loop)
  1215           ((member op '(:if :block :loop))
  1216            (format stream "~A(~A" spaces (string-downcase (symbol-name op)))
  1217            (when (and args (listp (first args)) (eq (first (first args)) :result))
  1218              (format stream " (result ~A)" (keyword-to-wat-type (second (first args))))
  1219              (setf args (rest args)))
  1220            (format stream "~%")
  1221            (dolist (sub-instr args)
  1222              (emit-instr-wat stream sub-instr (+ indent 2)))
  1223            (format stream "~A)~%" spaces))
  1224           ;; else is special
  1225           ((eq op :else)
  1226            (format stream "~Aelse~%" spaces))
  1227           ;; end is special
  1228           ((eq op :end)
  1229            (format stream "~Aend~%" spaces))
  1230           ;; ref.cast with type argument
  1231           ((eq op :ref.cast)
  1232            (if (listp (first args))
  1233                (format stream "~Aref.cast (ref ~A)~%" spaces (second (first args)))
  1234                ;; :i31 should be emitted as i31ref for WAT text format
  1235                (let ((type-arg (first args)))
  1236                  (format stream "~Aref.cast ~A~%" spaces
  1237                          (if (eq type-arg :i31) "i31ref" type-arg)))))
  1238           ;; ref.test with type argument
  1239           ((eq op :ref.test)
  1240            (if (listp (first args))
  1241                (format stream "~Aref.test (ref ~A)~%" spaces (second (first args)))
  1242                ;; :i31 should be emitted as i31ref for WAT text format
  1243                (let ((type-arg (first args)))
  1244                  (format stream "~Aref.test ~A~%" spaces
  1245                          (if (eq type-arg :i31) "i31ref" type-arg)))))
  1246           ;; ref.null
  1247           ((eq op :ref.null)
  1248            (format stream "~Aref.null ~A~%" spaces (string-downcase (symbol-name (first args)))))
  1249           ;; Regular instruction with operands
  1250           (t
  1251            (format stream "~A~A" spaces (string-downcase (symbol-name op)))
  1252            (dolist (arg args)
  1253              (format stream " ~A" arg))
  1254            (format stream "~%")))))
  1255      ;; Symbol (like :else or :end without parens)
  1256      ((symbolp instr)
  1257       (format stream "~A~A~%" spaces (string-downcase (symbol-name instr))))
  1258      ;; Shouldn't happen
  1259      (t
  1260       (format stream "~A;; unknown: ~S~%" spaces instr)))))
  1261
  1262(defun emit-module-wat (module)
  1263  "Emit a compiled module as WAT text."
  1264  (with-output-to-string (s)
  1265    (format s "(module~%")
  1266    ;; Types
  1267    (loop for func in (compiled-module-functions module)
  1268          for i from 0
  1269          do (format s "  (type $t~D (func" i)
  1270             (let ((params (getf func :params)))
  1271               (when params
  1272                 (format s " (param")
  1273                 (dolist (p params)
  1274                   (format s " ~A" (keyword-to-wat-type (second p))))
  1275                 (format s ")")))
  1276             (let ((result (getf func :result)))
  1277               (when result
  1278                 (format s " (result ~A)" (keyword-to-wat-type result))))
  1279             (format s "))~%"))
  1280    ;; Functions
  1281    (loop for func in (compiled-module-functions module)
  1282          for i from 0
  1283          do (format s "  (func $f~D (type $t~D)~%" i i)
  1284             ;; Emit locals
  1285             (let ((locals (getf func :locals)))
  1286               (when locals
  1287                 (dolist (local locals)
  1288                   (format s "    (local ~A)~%" (keyword-to-wat-type (second local))))))
  1289             ;; Emit body instructions
  1290             (let ((body (getf func :body)))
  1291               (dolist (instr body)
  1292                 (emit-instr-wat s instr 4)))
  1293             (format s "  )~%"))
  1294    ;; Exports
  1295    (dolist (export (compiled-module-exports module))
  1296      (destructuring-bind (name kind index) export
  1297        (format s "  (export ~S (~A $f~D))~%"
  1298                name
  1299                (ecase kind (:func "func") (:table "table") (:memory "memory") (:global "global"))
  1300                index)))
  1301    (format s ")~%")))
  1302
  1303(defun keyword-to-wat-type (type)
  1304  "Convert a type to WAT format.
  1305   Handles both keyword types and list-form reference types."
  1306  (cond
  1307    ;; List-form reference types: (:ref-null 2) -> (ref null 2)
  1308    ((and (listp type) (eq (first type) :ref-null))
  1309     (format nil "(ref null ~A)" (second type)))
  1310    ;; List-form non-null reference types: (:ref 2) -> (ref 2)
  1311    ((and (listp type) (eq (first type) :ref))
  1312     (format nil "(ref ~A)" (second type)))
  1313    ;; Simple keyword types
  1314    ((keywordp type)
  1315     (ecase type
  1316       (:i32 "i32")
  1317       (:i64 "i64")
  1318       (:f32 "f32")
  1319       (:f64 "f64")
  1320       (:anyref "anyref")
  1321       (:funcref "funcref")
  1322       (:i31ref "i31ref")
  1323       (:eqref "eqref")))
  1324    (t (error "Unknown type: ~A" type))))
  1325
  1326;;; ============================================================
  1327;;; Convenience Function
  1328;;; ============================================================
  1329
  1330(defun compile-expression (expr)
  1331  "Compile a single expression to Wasm instructions.
  1332   Returns the instruction list (for debugging)."
  1333  (let* ((ast (clysm/compiler/ast:parse-expr expr))
  1334         (env (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:make-env)))
  1335    (clysm/compiler/codegen/func-section:compile-to-instructions ast env)))
  1336
